gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 130, Wizards 104
gameRecap.excerpt: Boston defeats Washington, 130-104. For Boston, Sam Hauser led the way with a career-high 30 points, a career-high 10 3PM, and six rebounds while aided by Jayson Tatum (30 points, six rebounds, six assists, three steals) and Payton Pritchard (14 points, career-high 13 assists) in the victory. Jordan Poole finished with 31 points (three 3PM) and four assists with Justin Champagnie adding 14 points, eight rebounds, and two steals for the Wizards in the losing effort. Boston improves to 53-14, while Washington moves to 11-57 in the loss.
